## Data sources

### Phase 1 — Forward-looking (build now)
- New incident reports ingested going forward
- NYSCEF public records by index number (lookup only, not stored in full)
- Manual court contact verification
- No PII issues — index number encrypted on entry, internal ref used throughout

### Phase 2 — Backward-looking (later, carefully)
- Existing case files live in the firm's case management system
- Contains privileged communications, attorney notes, client data — cannot be touched directly
- Approach: human extracts only non-sensitive operational facts with proper access controls
- The encrypted index number connects existing cases to the operational layer without exposing data

